## ğŸ¯ Level Goal
A program is being executed automatically at regular intervals using
**cron**, the time-based job scheduler.

The task is to inspect the configuration files in
`/etc/cron.d/` and determine **which command is being run**.

---

## ğŸ” Explanation
Cron is used in Linux systems to schedule tasks that run automatically
in the background.

Configuration files inside `/etc/cron.d/` define jobs that are executed
at specific times or intervals, often with elevated privileges.

By reviewing these files, it is possible to identify scripts or commands
that handle sensitive data, such as passwords for the next level.

